System Logic

The laboratory runs continuously.

A subject may enter or not enter.

If the subject does not enter:
- no session opens
- no measurement occurs
- no record is created

If the subject enters:
- a session opens
- measurement occurs
- processing occurs
- a result is returned
- a record is created
- the session ends
- the laboratory continues

The laboratory does not push.
The laboratory does not interpret on behalf of the subject.
The laboratory records process and preserves trace.
